        { "x": 0, "y": 9, "to_map": "ash_approach", "to_x": 32, "to_y": 9 },
        { "x": 31, "y": 8, "to_map": "kiln_rim", "to_x": 1, "to_y": 8 },
        { "x": 31, "y": 9, "to_map": "kiln_rim", "to_x": 1, "to_y": 9 }
      ],
      "npcs": [
        {
          "id": "glassmaster_ferren",
          "x": 22,
          "y": 6,
          "name": "Glassmaster Ferren",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "when": { "relapsed": ["the_kiln", true] },
              "lines": [
                "My furnaces guttered last night — the draft's wrong all down the ridge. The Kiln is pulling air again.",
                "You quieted it once. Whatever crawled in after you means to finish what the Progenitors started. Please."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_kiln", "Purge"] },
              "lines": [
                "The Kiln's cold. The ridge is cooling with it — my furnaces run half-heat on wood and scavenge now.",
                "The trade will die in a generation. But no more war-stock walks out of that door, and my apprentices will die old. I've run the arithmetic. I sign it."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_kiln", "Reseed"] },
              "lines": [
                "The vents run gentle now — kiln-heat without the killing. My glass has never come out so clear.",
                "A whole valley warming its hands on a thing that was built to burn us. I laugh about it most days. Most days it isn't a nervous laugh."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_kiln", "Bind"] },
              "lines": [
                "They say the Kiln answers you now. That you grow your own stock in the vats we used to run from.",
                "Bring your beasts by the shop, rider. I'll blow glass eyes for the ones that lose theirs. Seems right that somebody up here still makes things that can't hurt anyone."
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "Caldera sand makes glass with fire already inside it. Every piece I blow holds a little of the mountain's temper.",
                "The Kiln taught us the trade, generations back, before it went to war-work. We kept the craft. It kept the fire."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "pyra_kid",
          "x": 10,
          "y": 12,
          "name": "Pyra",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_kiln", "Purge"] },
              "lines": [
                "The ground stopped grumbling. Everyone says that's good.",
                "I can't sleep without it. Don't tell Papa I said the mountain's name into the vent, just in case it's listening."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_kiln", "Bind"] },
              "lines": [
                "Is it true you can grow a salamber down there? A real one, just for you?",
                "If you grow one that's small and doesn't bite — I mean. If you ever need somebody to watch one. I'm just saying I'm available."
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "I sleep with a glass marble Master Ferren blew me. There's a little smoke curl trapped inside — see?",
                "Papa says the mountain grumbles because it's lonely. I grumble back so it isn't."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
